        <td class="NewsText" style="font-size: 15px">The first beta release of <a href="mageia">Mageia</a> 10, the upcoming major update of the project's general-purpose desktop Linux distribution, is now available for download and testing. It comes with Linux kernel 6.18, KDE Plasma 6.5 and GNOME 49. "<span class="Quote">Having been approved by the Council, the Mageia 10 beta 1 ISO images are now available for public testing. All together, about 26 GB of ISO images have landed in the /mageia/iso/10/ branch of our mirrors. A lot of fixes and new updates have been added since Mageia 10 alpha 1 arrived back in January. Following version freeze, here are notable changes from Mageia 9: Linux kernel 6.18 (LTS), KDE Plasma 6.5, GNOME 49, Xfce 4.20, LibreOffice 26.2, Firefox ESR 140.8, Mesa 26.0.2 enabling latest drivers for AMD, Intel and nouveau (NVIDIA proprietary drivers are available too). The plan is still to have the official Mageia 10 release ready in April 2026. The next steps include: publish beta 2 containing artwork and documentation updated for Mageia 10; increase tests, especially for upgrades from Mageia 9; concentrate on fixing release-blocker bugs.</span>" Here is the full <a href="https://blog.mageia.org/en/2026/03/20/we-are-proud-to-announce-the-first-beta-of-mageia-10/">release announcement</a>. <a href="https://www.mageia.org/en/downloads/prerelease/">Download</a> (<a href="table.php?distribution=mageia&pkglist=true&version=10-beta1#pkglist">pkglist</a>): <a href="https://ftp.belnet.be/mirror/mageia/mageia/iso/10/Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64/Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64.iso">Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64.iso</a> (5,302MB, <a href="https://ftp.belnet.be/mirror/mageia/mageia/iso/10/Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64/Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64.iso.sha512">SHA512</a>, <a href="https://ftp.belnet.be/mirror/mageia/mageia/iso/10/Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64/Mageia-10-beta1-x86_64.iso.sha512.gpg">signature</a>, <a href="https://distrib-coffee.ipsl.jussieu.fr/pub/linux/Mageia/iso/10/Mageia-10-beta1-x8